article.description: Warren Hall scored 24 points including the game-winner -- and five players reached double figures -- as NAIA Warner College never trailed while defeating Florida Atlantic 75-72 Tuesday night.
article.headline: NAIA Warner pops Florida Atlantic with 75-72 victory
article.linkText: NAIA Warner pops Florida Atlantic with 75-72 victory
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Warren Hall scored 24 points including the game-winner -- and five players reached double figures -- as NAIA Warner College never trailed while defeating Florida Atlantic 75-72 Tuesday night. Hall, who went over 1,000 career points last week, made 8 of 16 shots, including 2 of 3 from 3-point range for Warner (5-1). FAU (0-2) narrowed what had been a double-digit gap most of the game into a 72-72 tie in the final 1:13. Marquan Botley started the final run with a 3-point play and added four more free throws. Nick Rutherford hit a 3-pointer. But Hall buried a jumper and was fouled, converting the 3-point play with two seconds remaining. FAU missed a final 3-point try as time expired. Jeantal Cylla paced the Owls with 18 points, C.J. Turman scored 16 points with 11 rebounds for his first career double-double.
